What should I wear today?

Prologue

Meet Shawna. Every morning before university, she faces the same question: “What should I wear today?” To help her decide, we observed people’s outfit choices across seasons.

This visual story is based on data collected in Auckland.

What top should I wear?

During autumn,

  1. 65% of people wear a long-sleeved top
  2. 35% of people wear a short-sleeved top
  3. nobody wears a sleeveless top

During summer,

  1. 57% of people wear a short-sleeved top
  2. 29% of people wear a long-sleeved top
  3. 14% of people wear a sleeveless top

Let’s help Shawna decide what type of top to wear today!

About today:

  • Date: 13th May 2025
  • Season: Autumn

Seems like Shawna should wear a long-sleeved top today.

Now, what bottoms should I wear?

The most common length of bottoms for different temperature ranges has been summarised in the table below:

Temperature Range (°C) Length of Bottoms
15–19 Below the knees
20 Above the knees
21 Below the knees
22 Around the knees
22.5–23 Below the knees

Let’s inform Shawna about what bottoms to wear!

About today:

  • Current temperature: 16°C

Tell her to wear bottoms that reach below the knees so she can stay warm.

Wait, does my outfit look weird?

We consider a combination of top and bottoms to be “common” if more than 2 people (out of 44) have been seen wearing it. The common combinations of top and bottoms (in descending order) are:

Top Bottoms
1 Long-sleeved Below the knees
2 Short-sleeved Below the knees
3 Short-sleeved Around the knees
4 Short-sleeved Above the knees

Shawna is worried that her outfit looks weird!

About her outfit:

  • Long-sleeved top
  • Bottoms that reach below the knees

Not weird at all! In fact, that is how most people are dressed.

Epilogue

By exploring the clothing patterns of other Aucklanders, we created a simple guide to help Shawna pick outfits that balance comfort and style, appropriate for the season.

Thanks to a bit of data, Shawna is ready to head out the door with confidence! 😃
